feed.title: US corporate bond market is most competitive ever: Barclays
feed.summary: According to Barclays, the US corporate bond market is experiencing its most competitive conditions on record, driven by robust investor demand and a proliferation of funds. This increased competition is evident in both high-grade and junk bond markets, leading to more secondary market trading and lowered risk premiums. Barclays anticipates record new corporate bond issuance in 2026 due to various economic factors.

feed.title: Gartner: Will Entry-Level Jobs be Replaced by AI?
feed.summary: A Gartner report on the future of supply chains indicates that many leaders anticipate AI reducing the need for entry-level positions, thereby redefining roles and potentially workforce headcounts. While AI adoption will change how talent pipelines operate, high-performing organizations are focusing on redesigning roles, upskilling existing talent, and optimizing workforce planning with AI rather than simply reducing staff. This aims to create a workforce where humans and AI collaborate to generate value.

feed.title: Moderna (MRNA) Is Up 10.2% After FDA Accepts Full Review Of Its mRNA Flu Vaccine

feed.title: 1920-founded German insurer Krose sold to Arthur J. Gallagher
feed.summary: Arthur J. Gallagher & Co. (NYSE: AJG) announced the acquisition of Krose GmbH & Co KG, a German commercial insurance and reinsurance broker founded in 1920. The acquisition strengthens Gallagher's presence in Germany and Europe, expanding its offerings in property, casualty, cyber, marine, D&O, and alternative risk solutions. While the terms of the transaction were not disclosed, Krose's team of risk professionals will integrate into Gallagher's European brokerage operations.

feed.title: Boeing Company Proves AI Is a Better Sailor Than Humans Will Ever Be
feed.summary: Boeing's Aurora Flight Sciences, in collaboration with MIT, has developed FALCON, an AI-powered system that significantly improves ship safety during underway replenishment in challenging sea conditions. Demonstrations showed AI-assisted and AI-guided modes kept vessels in safe zones up to 94% of the time, compared to 63% for human control, and reduced recovery time by 61%. This technology, developed under DARPA's LINC program, has the potential to revolutionize control over maritime vessels, and eventually aircraft and land vehicles.
